entry.title: Tropical Storm Hilary Makes Landfall in Mexico, Threatening Southern California
entry.content: Hilary is on a track that forecasters say is likely to bring drenching rains beyond California into Nevada and even as far north as Boise, Idaho, over the next two days.

entry.title: Tropical Storm Hilary Poses Unusual Threat to Southern California
entry.content: The area, unaccustomed to tropical storms, is bracing for heavy rains and high winds.
